{
  "texts": [
    "Performance of Decoder ModelsTurning now to decoder models, we consider two code-pre-trained LLMs, Santacoder [1] and Codellama7B [29].",
    "We evaluate a custom 0.7B parameter Santacoder model obtained from the 1.1B teacher.",
    "Due to an inability to fine-tune on the full 24M coding examples, we use up to 1.2M.",
    "Fig. 5 shows that MLFS pass@1 improves rapidly as number of tokens increases from a low 10k to 400k to 1.2M examples, only 5% of the 24M examples.",
    "Table 1 shows analogous results with 3 small MLFS models."
  ]
}